# Eduket OS — Backend API
### AI-Powered School Assessment & Extraction Engine

[![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/Python-3.11+-blue.svg)](https://python.org)
[![Flask](https://img.shields.io/badge/Flask-3.x-green.svg)](https://flask.palletsprojects.com)
[![Firebase](https://img.shields.io/badge/Firebase-Admin_SDK-orange.svg)](https://firebase.google.com)
[![Render](https://img.shields.io/badge/Deployed_on-Render-purple.svg)](https://render.com)
[![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-Proprietary-red.svg)](LICENSE)

---

## Overview

The Eduket OS backend is a production Flask API that powers Africa's first AI-driven school assessment operating system. It handles exam document extraction, AI-based marking, real-time analysis, billing, and a multi-provider AI coaching interface for learners.

Teachers upload Word documents. The backend converts them, renders every page, extracts questions using vision AI, and delivers fully marked, individually analysed results — within minutes of a student submitting.

---

## Architecture

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    Eduket OS Backend                         │
│                   (Flask on Render)                          │
│                                                              │
│  ┌─────────────┐    ┌──────────────────┐    ┌───────────┐  │
│  │  Flask API  │───▶│ extraction_engine│───▶│LibreOffice│  │
│  │  app.py     │    │ (render-first)   │    │ headless  │  │
│  └──────┬──────┘    └────────┬─────────┘    └───────────┘  │
│         │                    │                               │
│  ┌──────▼──────┐    ┌────────▼─────────┐    ┌───────────┐  │
│  │  Billing    │    │   PyMuPDF        │    │Groq Vision│  │
│  │  Routes     │    │  Page Renderer   │───▶│+ Gemini   │  │
│  └─────────────┘    └──────────────────┘    └───────────┘  │
│                                                              │
│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │
│  │            AI Provider Chain                         │    │
│  │  Groq (primary) → Gemini (fallback)                 │    │
│  │  Auto model resolution · Auto fallback · Retry      │    │
│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │
└──────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────┘
                           │
              ┌────────────▼────────────┐
              │     Firebase            │
              │  Firestore · Auth       │
              │  Storage · Admin SDK    │
              └─────────────────────────┘
```

---

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology | Purpose |
|-------|------------|---------|
| Runtime | Python 3.11+ | Core language |
| Web framework | Flask 3.x + Flask-CORS | REST API |
| Server | Gunicorn (gthread) | Production WSGI server |
| Document conversion | LibreOffice headless | DOCX/ODT → PDF |
| PDF rendering | PyMuPDF (fitz) | PDF → page images at 200 DPI |
| AI — vision | Groq `llama-4-scout-17b-16e-instruct` | Page image → question JSON |
| AI — text (primary) | Groq (auto-resolved model) | Marking, analysis, parsing |
| AI — text (fallback) | Google Gemini 2.0 Flash | Automatic failover |
| Database | Firebase Firestore (Admin SDK) | All persistent data |
| Storage | Firebase Storage (Admin SDK) | Exam files + page images |
| Authentication | Firebase Auth (token verification) | All route auth |
| Billing | PayFast | ZAR payment processing |
| Deployment | Render.com | Cloud hosting |

