## Environment Variables

Create a `.env` file in the project root (never commit this file):

```bash
# ── Firebase ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Paste the full service account JSON as a single-line string, OR provide
# the path to a local JSON file. Render uses the inline string approach.
FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON='{"type":"service_account","project_id":"..."}'

# Firebase Storage bucket name (without gs:// prefix)
FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=your-project.firebasestorage.app

# ── AI Providers ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Groq — primary AI provider (console.groq.com)
GROQ_API_KEY=gsk_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# Google Gemini — automatic fallback (aistudio.google.com — free tier)
GEMINI_API_KEY=AIzaSyxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# ── PayFast Billing ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Never commit these. All three required for payment processing.
PAYFAST_MERCHANT_ID=12345678
PAYFAST_MERCHANT_KEY=xxxxxxxxxxxx
PAYFAST_PASSPHRASE=your_secure_passphrase_here

# ── URLs ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Production frontend origin (no trailing slash — browsers never send one)
FRONTEND_BASE_URL=https://eduket.tech

# This backend's own URL (used for PayFast notify_url in ITN handler)
BACKEND_BASE_URL=https://your-service.onrender.com

# ── Server ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
PORT=10000
```

> **Render deployment:** Set all variables above in your Render service dashboard under **Environment**. Never use a `.env` file in production — Render injects them as real environment variables.

