## Local Development Setup

### Prerequisites
- Python 3.11+
- LibreOffice (for document conversion)
- Firebase project with Firestore, Storage, and Auth enabled

### Installation

```bash
# 1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/nextgenskills/eduket-backend.git
cd eduket-backend

# 2. Create and activate a virtual environment
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # Windows: venv\Scripts\activate

# 3. Install Python dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# 4. Install LibreOffice (required for document conversion)
# Ubuntu/Debian:
sudo apt-get install -y libreoffice --no-install-recommends

# macOS:
brew install --cask libreoffice

# 5. Copy environment variable template and fill in your values
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env with your actual credentials

# 6. Run the development server
python app.py
# Server starts on http://localhost:10000
```

### Verify setup

```bash
# Check the health endpoint
curl http://localhost:10000/
# Expected: {"status": "ok", "service": "Eduket Extraction & Marking API", "version": "5.0"}

# Verify LibreOffice is accessible
libreoffice --version
# Expected: LibreOffice 7.x.x ...

# Check Firebase connection (should print ✅ Ready in server logs)
# If Firebase initialization fails the server exits with SystemExit(1)
```

