## API Reference

All endpoints require a valid Firebase ID token in the `Authorization` header unless marked as public.

```
Authorization: Bearer <firebase_id_token>
```

### Health

```
GET /
```
Public. Returns service status and version. Used by the frontend keep-alive ping.

**Response:**
```json
{
  "status": "ok",
  "service": "Eduket Extraction & Marking API",
  "version": "5.0"
}
```

---

### Exam Upload

```
POST /exams/upload
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <token>
```

Creates the exam record in Firestore and immediately triggers the extraction pipeline in a background thread. Does not wait for extraction to complete.

**Request body:**
```json
{
  "examId":          "uid_timestamp",
  "title":           "Grade 12 Maths Paper 1",
  "subject":         "Mathematics",
  "grade":           "Grade 12",
  "year":            "2026",
  "curriculum":      "CAPS",
  "examDuration":    90,
  "examFileName":    "Maths_P1.docx",
  "examStoragePath": "exams/schoolFolder/subject/examId/exam_Maths_P1.docx",
  "examStorageUrl":  "https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/...",
  "memoFileName":    "Maths_P1_memo.docx",
  "memoStoragePath": "exams/.../memo_Maths_P1_memo.docx",
  "memoStorageUrl":  "https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/...",
  "aiMarkingOnly":   false,
  "schoolFolder":    "schoolId_SchoolName",
  "schoolName":      "Prince Edward High",
  "teacherName":     "Mr Zulu"
}
```

**Response:**
```json
{ "examId": "uid_timestamp", "duplicate": false }
```

**Error responses:**
```json
{ "error": "limit_reached", "message": "...", "tier": "free", "limit": 5, "used": 5 }  // 403
{ "error": "User profile not found" }  // 404
{ "error": "School not found" }        // 404
```

> **Firestore index required:** `exams` collection — composite index on `schoolId ASC, uploadedAt ASC`. Without it this route returns 500. Create the index in the Firebase Console → Firestore → Indexes.

---

### Exam Usage

```
GET /exams/usage
Authorization: Bearer <token>
```

Returns the school's monthly exam upload count against their tier limit.

**Response:**
```json
{
  "tier":      "gold",
  "limit":     120,
  "used":      14,
  "remaining": 106,
  "atLimit":   false
}
```

