### List Exams

```
GET /exams
```

Returns all exams with `status: "ready"`. Used by student dashboard to populate the exam selector.

**Response:**
```json
{
  "exams": [
    {
      "id":           "examId",
      "name":         "Grade 12 Maths Paper 1",
      "subject":      "Mathematics",
      "grade":        "Grade 12",
      "year":         "2026",
      "curriculum":   "CAPS",
      "memoMerged":   true,
      "examDuration": 90
    }
  ]
}
```

---

### Start Exam

```
POST /start_exam
Content-Type: application/json
```

Creates an in-memory session for a student attempt. Returns all questions with rich content fields.

**Request body:**
```json
{ "exam_id": "examId", "student_id": "studentUid" }
```

**Response:**
```json
{
  "session_id":            "uuid",
  "questions":             [...],
  "total_questions":       18,
  "memo_merged":           true,
  "subject":               "Mathematics",
  "title":                 "Grade 12 Maths Paper 1",
  "exam_duration_minutes": 90
}
```

Each question in the array includes:
```json
{
  "question_number": "1.1",
  "question":        "Calculate the value of x if...",
  "type":            "calculation",
  "marks":           4,
  "options":         null,
  "questionImageUrl": "https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/...",
  "hasVisual":        true,
  "questionLatex":    "$x^2 + 3x - 10 = 0$",
  "questionTable":    null
}
```

> **Important:** Memo answers are NOT returned to the student before submission. The `memo` field is stripped from the session data before the response is sent.

---

### Save Answer

```
POST /answer
Content-Type: application/json
```

Saves a single answer to the session. Called after every question to support autosave.

**Request body:**
```json
{ "session_id": "uuid", "index": 0, "answer": "B" }
```

---

### Submit Exam

```
POST /submit
Content-Type: application/json
```

Marks all answers, generates per-question feedback, runs cognitive analysis, and returns complete results. This is the most computationally expensive endpoint — allow up to 60 seconds for a 20-question paper.

**Request body:**
```json
{
  "exam_id":    "examId",
  "student_id": "studentUid",
  "answers":    { "0": "B", "1": "True", "2": "RAM is volatile..." }
}
```

**Response:**
```json
{
  "score":      34,
  "total":      50,
  "percentage": 68.0,
  "subject":    "Computer Science",
  "feedback":   "Good effort. A solid attempt...",
  "analysis": {
    "overallSummary":    "...",
    "strengths":         ["..."],
    "weaknesses":        ["..."],
    "misconceptions":    ["..."],
    "cognitiveAnalysis": { "remember": 80, "understand": 60, "apply": 40, ... },
    "studyPlan":         ["..."],
    "teacherSummary":    "...",
    "parentSummary":     "..."
  },
  "results": [
    {
      "question_number": "1.1",
      "question":        "What does RAM stand for?",
      "type":            "short_answer",
      "marks":           2,
      "earned":          2,
      "status":          "correct",
      "student_answer":  "Random Access Memory",
      "correct_answer":  "Random Access Memory",
      "feedback":        "Correct.",
      "concept_gap":     "",
      "model_answer":    "Random Access Memory"
    }
  ]
}
```

**Marking logic:**
1. Rule-based marking against memo answer (exact match, fuzzy similarity ≥ 0.75, MCQ letter, True/False)
2. AI marking fallback when memo is absent, inconclusive, or similarity < 0.75
3. Spelling errors are forgiven — conceptual understanding is evaluated

---

### Autosave

```
POST /autosave
GET  /autosave/<exam_id>/<student_id>
```

Saves and restores in-progress exam answers. Prevents data loss on browser refresh.

---

### AI Remark

```
POST /remark
Content-Type: application/json
```

Re-marks one or more questions using AI. Used when a teacher disputes a mark.

**Request body:**
```json
{
  "subject": "Mathematics",
  "results": [
    {
      "question":        "Calculate x...",
      "student_answer":  "x = 2 or x = -5",
      "correct_answer":  "x = 2 or x = -5",
      "marks":           4
    }
  ]
}
```

---

### AI Study Coach

```
POST /agent-chat
Content-Type: application/json
```

Real-time AI academic coaching. The coach is aware of the student's results, subject, and weak areas.

**Request body:**
```json
{
  "student_id":      "uid",
  "message":         "I don't understand how to factorise",
  "learningProfile": { "subjects": ["Mathematics"], "overallAverage": 62, "weakAreas": [...] },
  "latestAttempt":   { "examTitle": "Maths P1", "percentage": 58, "markedResults": [...] },
  "history":         [{ "role": "user", "content": "..." }, { "role": "assistant", "content": "..." }]
}
```

---

### Admin Routes

These routes are for internal use during development and production debugging.

```
GET /admin/extraction-status/<exam_id>
```
Returns current extraction status, question count, and whether the exam is student-accessible.

```
GET /admin/trigger-extract/<exam_id>
```
Manually re-triggers extraction for a stuck exam. Use when `status` is `error` or has been `pending_extraction` for more than 5 minutes. After calling this, poll `/admin/extraction-status/<exam_id>` until status is `extracted`.

```
POST /admin/cleanup-sessions
```
Deletes exam sessions older than 24 hours. Run periodically to keep `exam_sessions` collection clean.

---

### Billing Routes

Registered via `billing_bp` blueprint. All billing routes are prefixed `/api/billing/`.

| Route | Method | Description |
|-------|--------|-------------|
| `/api/billing/quote` | POST | Price quote for a single tier |
| `/api/billing/quotes` | GET | Quotes for all tiers at once |
| `/api/billing/initiate` | POST | Create pending transaction + PayFast form data |
| `/api/payfast/itn` | POST | PayFast ITN webhook — upgrades school tier |

> **Security:** The ITN handler is the sole authority for tier upgrades. It verifies the PayFast signature, confirms the payment amount matches the pending transaction, and only then writes the new tier to `schools/{schoolId}` via the Admin SDK.

---

## Firestore Schema

### Collections written by the backend

```
exams/{examId}
  ├── examId, title, subject, grade, curriculum
  ├── uploadedBy, teacherName, schoolId, schoolFolder
  ├── examDuration, examStoragePath, memoStoragePath
  ├── status: "pending_extraction" | "processing" | "extracted" | "error"
  ├── questionsExtracted: bool
  ├── memoMerged: bool
  ├── totalQuestions: int
  └── extractedAt: timestamp

exam_questions/{examId}_{nnnn}
  ├── examId, questionNumber, parentQuestion, parentContext
  ├── section, questionText, type, marks
  ├── options: {A, B, C, D} | null
  ├── columnA, columnB (for matching questions)
  ├── memo: string (answer — not sent to student before submission)
  ├── order: int
  ├── questionImageUrl: string | null  (Firebase Storage URL for page PNG)
  ├── hasVisual: bool
  ├── questionLatex: string | null     (LaTeX for maths equations)
  └── questionTable: string | null     (Markdown for accounting tables)

exam_sessions/{sessionId}
  ├── exam_id, exam, subject, student_id
  ├── questions: [...] (full question array, no memos)
  └── answers: {index: answer}

exam_autosaves/{examId}_{studentId}
  ├── examId, studentId
  └── answers: {index: answer}

exam_pages/{schoolFolder}/{examId}/page_{nnn}.png
  └── (Firebase Storage — page renders for visual questions)

teacherExamUploads/{schoolId}/subjects/{subject}
  └── uploads: [{examId, status, ...}, ...]

paymentTransactions/{paymentId}
  ├── schoolId, tierId, fromTier, billingCycle
  ├── expectedAmount (ZAR), expectedCurrency: "ZAR"
  ├── displayAmount (local), displayCurrency
  └── status: "pending" | "complete"
```

---

## Firestore Indexes Required

Create these in **Firebase Console → Firestore → Indexes → Composite**:

| Collection | Fields | Required by |
|------------|--------|-------------|
| `exams` | `schoolId ASC, uploadedAt ASC` | `/exams/upload` monthly count |
| `exam_attempts` | `schoolId ASC, completedAt DESC` | Teacher results tab |
| `exam_attempts` | `schoolId ASC, subject ASC, completedAt DESC` | Subject-filtered results |

**Collection group index:**
| Collection group | Field | Required by |
|-----------------|-------|-------------|
| `subjects` | (any field) | Startup sweep + Firestore listener |

> When an index is missing, Firestore returns a `FailedPrecondition` error with a direct link to create it. This link appears in Render logs — click it to create the index automatically.

---

## Deployment (Render)

### Build command

```bash
apt-get install -y libreoffice --no-install-recommends && pip install -r requirements.txt
```

LibreOffice (~400MB) must be installed at build time. Without it the extraction pipeline falls back to text-only parsing and cannot process embedded images or equations.

### Start command

```bash
gunicorn app:app --config gunicorn.conf.py
```

### `gunicorn.conf.py`

```python
workers     = 2
worker_class = "gthread"
threads     = 4
timeout     = 120          # extraction can take up to 90 seconds for large papers
bind        = "0.0.0.0:10000"
preload_app = False        # must be False — Firebase Admin SDK initialises per-worker
```

> **Note:** `preload_app = True` causes the Firebase Admin SDK to share a single gRPC connection across forked worker processes, which breaks Firestore listeners. Keep it `False`.

### Environment variables (set in Render dashboard)

```
FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON  (paste full JSON as single-line string)
FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET
GROQ_API_KEY
GEMINI_API_KEY
PAYFAST_MERCHANT_ID
PAYFAST_MERCHANT_KEY
PAYFAST_PASSPHRASE
FRONTEND_BASE_URL              https://eduket.tech
BACKEND_BASE_URL               https://your-service.onrender.com
PORT                           10000
```

### Verify deployment

After deploying, confirm these lines appear in Render logs:

```
[Firebase] project_id : your-project-id
[Firebase] ✅ Ready
[Model] Groq model resolved: llama-3.1-70b-versatile
[Listener] Active — watching all subjects
[Startup] Sweep complete — N extraction(s) launched
```

---

## Security Architecture

### Authentication flow

Every protected route calls `verify_request_token(request)` first. This verifies the Firebase ID token server-side using the Admin SDK. The decoded token provides the `uid` — **no client-supplied uid is ever trusted**.

```python
uid, err = verify_request_token(request)
if err:
    return err  # returns 401 immediately
# uid is now verified from the token
```

### schoolId derivation

The `schoolId` for any school-scoped operation is **always** derived from the authenticated user's Firestore document (`users/{uid}.schoolId`), never from the request body. This prevents a malicious actor from sending a different `schoolId` to access another school's data.

### Billing security

- **Client cannot upgrade tier** — `schools/{schoolId}.tier` is write-protected in Firestore rules. Only the ITN handler can write it via the Admin SDK.
- **ITN signature verification** — every PayFast notification is verified using MD5 signature + passphrase before any action is taken.
- **Amount verification** — the ITN handler confirms `amount_gross` matches the amount stored in `paymentTransactions/{id}` within ±0.01 ZAR (floating point tolerance).
- **PayFast always receives ZAR** — international schools see local currency in the UI but PayFast always processes in ZAR. The `amountZarEquivalent` field is what gets submitted.

### CORS

```python
CORS(app, resources={r"/*": {
    "origins": [
        "https://eduket.tech",      # no trailing slash
        "http://localhost:5173",     # dev only
        ...
    ],
    "methods":       ["GET", "POST", "PUT", "DELETE", "OPTIONS"],
    "allow_headers": ["Content-Type", "Authorization"],
}})
```

**Note:** The `@app.before_request` OPTIONS handler was removed — it conflicted with Flask-CORS and caused header mismatches on preflights. Flask-CORS handles OPTIONS correctly on its own.

---

## Troubleshooting

### Exam stuck in `pending_extraction`

1. Check Render logs for `[Listener] Error` — the collection group index may be missing.
2. Manually trigger: `GET /admin/trigger-extract/<examId>`
3. Poll status: `GET /admin/extraction-status/<examId>`
4. Look for `[LibreOffice] Not installed` in logs — build command may be missing the `apt-get` prefix.

### "No questions could be extracted"

1. Check `[Model] Groq model resolved:` in logs — if it shows a model that was decommissioned, invalidate the cache by restarting the service.
2. Check `[Parser] Chunk 1: Error code: 413` — chunk size too large. The 413 retry with half-chunk should handle this automatically.
3. Check `[Gemini] Failed:` — confirms Gemini fallback was tried. Verify `GEMINI_API_KEY` is set.
4. Confirm LibreOffice is installed: the log should show `[LibreOffice] <filename> → PDF (NNNNN bytes)`, not `Not installed`.

### CORS errors on `/exams/upload`

1. Confirm `FRONTEND_BASE_URL` in Render has no trailing slash — `https://eduket.tech` not `https://eduket.tech/`.
2. Confirm the PWA service worker has `NetworkOnly` rule for cross-origin requests in `vite.config.js`.
3. Confirm `@app.before_request` OPTIONS handler is removed from `app.py`.

### PayFast "403 Forbidden" on payment

1. Confirm `PAYFAST_MERCHANT_ID` and `PAYFAST_MERCHANT_KEY` are set in Render env vars.
2. Confirm `PAYFAST_PASSPHRASE` matches exactly what is set in the PayFast merchant dashboard.
3. Confirm `BACKEND_BASE_URL` is set — the `notify_url` is built from this value.
4. Confirm the notify URL domain is whitelisted in the PayFast merchant dashboard under **Settings → Integration**.
5. Confirm `currency` field is NOT in the PayFast form POST — PayFast has no such parameter and rejects unknown fields.

### Firebase initialization fails

1. Confirm `FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON` is a valid single-line JSON string (not a file path in production).
2. Confirm `private_key` field contains actual newlines, not the literal string `\n`. The `_init_firebase()` function handles this replacement automatically.
3. Confirm the service account has the required Firebase roles: **Firebase Admin SDK Administrator Service Agent**.

---

## Monitoring

### Key log markers to watch in Render

| Log line | Meaning |
|----------|---------|
| `[Firebase] ✅ Ready` | Firebase initialized successfully |
| `[Model] Groq model resolved: <model>` | AI model selected for this deployment |
| `[Listener] Active` | Firestore extraction listener is watching |
| `[Pipeline] ═══ <examId>` | Extraction started for an exam |
| `[Pipeline] ✓ Done — N questions` | Extraction completed successfully |
| `[Pipeline] FAILED: <error>` | Extraction failed — check errorMessage in Firestore |
| `[AI] Gemini fallback responded` | Groq failed, Gemini took over |
| `[Groq] Model decommissioned — re-resolving` | Auto model rotation triggered |

### Recommended checks after each deployment

```bash
# 1. Health check
curl https://your-service.onrender.com/

# 2. Trigger a known-good exam extraction
curl https://your-service.onrender.com/admin/trigger-extract/<knownExamId>

# 3. Check extraction completed
curl https://your-service.onrender.com/admin/extraction-status/<knownExamId>
```

